t the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["form of   John  , also used quite frequently in the English-speaking world. In Northern Ireland it is sometimes found as a variant of   Ewan ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Joan was born about 1207, in Bedfordshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Peter III de Goldington."},"et":{"ABT 1207–":"umbes 1207–Surnud","1200–1252":"1200–1252","1127–1148":"1127–1148","1207–Female":"1207–Surnud","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1200":"1200","1252":"1252","ABT 1207":"umbes 1207","1207":"1207",", BEDFORDSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Bedfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1207–":"noin 1207–Kuollut","1200–1252":"1200–1252","1127–1148":"1127–1148","1207–Female":"1207–Kuollut","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1200":"1200","1252":"1252","ABT 1207":"noin 1207","1207":"1207",", BEDFORDSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Bedfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT 1207–":"environ 1207–Décédée","1200–1252":"1200–1252","1127–1148":"1127–1148","1207–Female":"1207–Décédée","1127":"1127","1148":"1148","1200":"1200","1252":"1252","ABT 1207":"environ 1207","1207":"1207",", BEDFORDSHIRE, ENGLAND":"Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Joan est née environ 1207, à Bedfordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Sir Peter III de Goldington."},"de":{"ABT 1207–":"um 1207–Verstorben","1200–1252":"1200–1252","1127–1148":"1127–1148","1207–Female":"1207–Verstorben","1127":"1127","114